        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 1:07AM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 107 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Columbia Falls, or 15 miles north of Evergreen, moving northeast at
45 mph.

HAZARD...Half-inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Whitefish, Columbia Falls, West Glacier, Apgar, Martin City, Coram,
Polebridge, Hungry Horse, and Lake McDonald.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 2 between mile markers 132 and 162.
Highway 93 N between mile markers 125 and 131, and between mile
markers 133 and 134.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
